
[1]thousand

   THOU'SAND, a. s as z.

   1. Denoting the number of ten hundred.

   2. Proverbially, denoting a great number indefinitely. It is a thousand
   chances to one that you succeed.

                  THOU'SAND, n. The number of ten hundred.

   A thousand shall fall at thy side, and ten thousand at thy right hand.
   Ps.91.

   Thousand is sometimes used plurally without the plural termination, as
      in the passage above, ten thousand; but it often takes the plural
    termination. In former times, how many thousands perished by famine!
